text:
We will now start the test portion

In this experiment you will see at least green shape on the left side of the screen, and a white shape on the right.

You will be asked to judge whether the green shape on the left is the same the white shape on the right.

If the shapes are the same, please press the M Key. If the shapes are different, press the Z Key.

On some trials, a red shape will overlap the green shape. Ignore this red shape, your job is to match the green shape to the white shape.

On some trials, you will see a star appear at the same time, or shortly after, the shapes appear. Do not respond if you see a star.

If the star appears on a trial, and you try your best to withhold your response, you will find that you will be able to stop sometimes but not always.

Do not slow down your responses to the shapes in order to wait for the star.

You will no longer receive the rule prompt, so remember the instructions before you continue. Press Enter to begin.

Please read the following paragraph:

“I never believed in Santa Claus. None of us kids did. Mom and Dad refused to let us. They couldn’t afford expensive presents and they didn’t want us to think we weren’t as good as other kids who, on Christmas morning, found all sorts of fancy toys under the tree that were supposedly left by Santa Claus. Dad had lost his job at the gypsum, and when Christmas came that year, we had no money at all. On Christmas Eve, Dad took each one of us kids out into the desert night one by one.

"If you are reading this paragraph, press the letter V," Dad Said.

“I like that one!” I said.

Dad grinned, “that’s Venus”, he said. He explained to me that planets glowed because reflected light was constant and stars twinkled because their light pulsed.

“I like it anyway” I said.

“What the heck,” Dad said. “It’s Christmas. You can have a planet if you want.”

And he gave me Venus. -- The Glass Castle (Jeannette Walls)
